  "prompt": "What are the best ways to humbly respond when someone compliments your looks or attire?",
  "response": "Here are some gracious ways to respond to compliments about your appearance or attire:\n\n1. Simple and direct responses\n- \"Thank you, that's very kind\"\n- \"I appreciate that\"\n- \"Thank you so much\"\n\n2. Warm and genuine responses\n- \"That's really nice of you to say\"\n- \"Thank you, you made my day\"\n- \"I'm glad you like it\"\n\n3. Slightly self-deprecating but lighthearted responses\n- \"Oh, this old thing?\"\n- \"Thanks, I just got lucky today\"\n- \"I'm just trying my best\"\n\n4. Reciprocal and positive responses\n- \"Thank you! I like your outfit too\"\n- \"That's sweet of you to notice\"\n\n5. Brief and sincere acknowledgments\n- \"Thank you, that's very kind\"\n- \"I appreciate the compliment\"\n\nKey tips:\n- Smile genuinely\n- Make eye contact\n- Avoid dismissing the compliment\n- Don't overexplain or become self-conscious\n- Keep your response relatively brief\n- Show gratitude\n\nThe goal is to be gracious, humble, and appreciative without appearing overly modest or uncomfortable.",
